The paper discusses environment modeling in autonomous driving, which is a topic related to robotics and computer vision. Therefore, cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also presents a fusion algorithm that combines different representations of the environment, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely sub-category as well. The fusion algorithm also generates new hypotheses, which can be seen as a form of learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with tracking objects over time, which is a topic related to control systems, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible sub-category.
